				\begin{document}$$u=({V}_{t{\rm{n}}+1}-{V}_{t{\rm{n}}})/{\rm{\Delta }}{\rm{T}}$$\end{document}u=(Vtn+1−Vtn)/ΔTwhere for (1) ΔS is the range of distribution shift; St represents the suitable area at time ‘t’; tn represents time for different periods (four periods in total: LIG, LGM, current, and future); ΔT equals the years from the periods tn to tn+1, ΔT1 ≈ 98,000 (from LIG to LGM), ΔT2 ≈ 22,000 (LGM to current), ΔT3 ≈ 75 (current to future) and for (2) u equals the variation rate of elevation (ualt) or longitude and latitude of distribution center (ulon and ulat) and Vt equals the mean elevation or mean center at time ‘t’.
